	abstract = {Triggering final oocyte maturation is a pivotal step in modern patient-tailored IVF/ICSI treatment, securing the optimal number of mature oocytes retrieved without compromising fertilization, embryo development, and live birth. Several factors need to be considered when deciding the time of the trigger: the size of the leading follicles, distribution of the follicular cohort, the duration of stimulation, the protocol used for stimulation, and ovarian response status.},
